# Session 84 Summary (2026-02-27)

**Commits:** 10 on feature/examark-qti | **Tests:** 3,302 (3,165 Jest + 137 node:test), 136 suites

**Completed (Canvas QTI Enhancements E1-E7):**
- E1: Upload→Essay mapping with warning — `file-upload` questions degrade to Essay with prepended note, warnings surfaced via `formatter.warnings`
- E2: Rich demo fixture — `quiz-mixed.json` covering all 10 question types (MC, MA, TF, Short, Numeric, Essay, Match, FMB, FIB, Upload)
- E3: Verify tolerance — `_parseExamarkWarnings()` separates expected "No correct answer" warnings from real errors; `validateQTI()` returns `{ valid, errors, warnings }`
- E4: Section/question group support — H1 sections propagate as `sectionName`, ExamarkFormatter emits H1 headers when section changes (Canvas maps to question groups)
- E5: Point redistribution — verified already correct (sub-parts divide equally), added 3 regression tests
- E6: Matching distractors — deferred (examark ignores distractors)
- E7: Image support — `extractImages()` finds `![alt](path)`, `sourceDir` option threads CWD to examark CLI for image bundling
- Fixed cache race condition in discovery tests (snapshot cache data in `before()` hook)
- Updated discovery counts (31→32, 17→18) across 3 test files
- Documentation: Canvas QTI guide, What's New release notes, mkdocs.yml nav

**New tests:** 45 examark formatter + 7 canvas formatter + 11 QMD parser + 31 e2e canvas QTI + 3 dogfood

